      "applicationProcess": [
        {
          "mode": "Offline",
          "process": [
            {
              "type": "align_justify",
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "ul_list",
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "list_item",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "To avail the benefits of the scheme, the applicant must submit an application to the office of the Assistant Director of Fisheries/District Fisheries In-charge at the district level. The application should be submitted along with the following documents: Aadhaar card, land records, permanent residence certificate, caste certificate, bank account details, and mobile number."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "list_item",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "In the future, the application process will be made available online through the ",
                          "italic": true,
                          "bold": true
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "link",
                          "link": "https://eservices.uk.gov.in/",
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "italic": true,
                              "bold": true,
                              "text": "Apuni Sarkar Portal"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "italic": true,
                          "bold": true,
                          "text": "."
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "list_item",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "text": "After the application is submitted, a survey is conducted by the Fisheries Inspector/field personnel, and a proposal is prepared in consultation with the beneficiary. Once the proposal is finalized, the concerned district officer approves the work. Field personnel then supervise the implementation and provide technical assistance to ensure timely completion. Subsequently, the subsidy is transferred directly to the beneficiary’s bank account through DBT."
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "process_md": "\n  - To avail the benefits of the scheme, the applicant must submit an application to the office of the Assistant Director of Fisheries/District Fisheries In-charge at the district level. The application should be submitted along with the following documents: Aadhaar card, land records, permanent residence certificate, caste certificate, bank account details, and mobile number.\n  - ***In the future, the application process will be made available online through the*** [***Apuni Sarkar Portal***](https://eservices.uk.gov.in/)***.***  - After the application is submitted, a survey is conducted by the Fisheries Inspector/field personnel, and a proposal is prepared in consultation with the beneficiary. Once the proposal is finalized, the concerned district officer approves the work. Field personnel then supervise the implementation and provide technical assistance to ensure timely completion. Subsequently, the subsidy is transferred directly to the beneficiary’s bank account through DBT.\n\n<br>\n\n"
        }
      ],
